		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Socialist realism</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">Not to be confused with <a href="/wiki/Social_realism" title="Social realism">Social realism</a>&#160;or <a href="/wiki/Real_socialism" title="Real socialism">Real socialism</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Roses_for_Stalin_by_Vladimirskij.jpg" class="image" title="&quot;Roses for Stalin&quot;, Boris Vladimirski, 1949"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c6/Roses_for_Stalin_by_Vladimirskij.jpg/300px-Roses_for_Stalin_by_Vladimirskij.jpg" width="300" height="212" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Roses_for_Stalin_by_Vladimirskij.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
"Roses for Stalin", <a href="/wiki/Boris_Vladimirski" title="Boris Vladimirski">Boris Vladimirski</a>, 1949</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Socialist realism</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Teleology" title="Teleology">teleologically</a>-oriented style of <a href="/wiki/Realism_(arts)" title="Realism (arts)">realistic art</a> which has as its purpose the furtherance of the goals of <a href="/wiki/Socialism" title="Socialism">socialism</a> and <a href="/wiki/Communism" title="Communism">communism</a>. Although related, it should not be confused with <a href="/wiki/Social_realism" title="Social realism">social realism</a>, a type of art that realistically depicts subjects of social concern.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
