<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Socialist_realism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: References and further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References and further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Bek, Mikuláš, Geoffrey Chew, and Petr Macek (eds.). <i>Socialist Realism and Music</i>. Musicological Colloquium at the Brno International Music Festival 36. Prague: KLP; Brno: Institute of Musicology, Masaryk University, 2004. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/8086791181" class="internal">ISBN 8086791181</a></li>
<li>Golomstock, Igor. <i>Totalitarian Art in the Soviet Union, the Third Reich, Fascist Italy and the People's Republic of China</i>, Harper Collins, 1990.</li>
<li>James, C. Vaughan. <i>Soviet Socialist Realism: Origins and Theory</i>. New York: St. Martin's Press, 1973.</li>
<li>Prokhorov, Gleb. <i>Art under Socialist Realism: Soviet Painting, 1930-1950</i>. East Roseville, NSW, Australia: Craftsman House; G + B Arts International, 1995. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9768097833" class="internal">ISBN 9768097833</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Andrei_Sinyavsky" title="Andrei Sinyavsky">Sinyavsky, Andrei</a> [writing as Abram Tertz]. <i>"The Trial Begins", and "On Socialist Realism"</i>, translated by Max Hayward and George Dennis, with an introduction by <a href="/wiki/Czes%C5%82aw_Mi%C5%82osz" title="Czesław Miłosz">Czesław Miłosz</a>. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1960–1982. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0520046773" class="internal">ISBN 0-520-04677-3</a></li>
</ul>
